Quick Overview
**************

Pretty Good(tm) Privacy (PGP), from Phil's Pretty Good Software, is a high
security cryptographic software application for MSDOS, Unix, VAX/VMS, and
other computers.  PGP combines the convenience of the
Rivest-Shamir-Adleman (RSA) public key cryptosystem with the speed of
conventional cryptography, message digests for digital signatures, data
compression before encryption, good ergonomic design, and sophisticated
key management.

This volume II of the PGP User's Guide covers advanced topics about PGP
that were not covered in the "PGP User's Guide, Volume I: Essential
Topics".  You should first read the Essential Topics volume, or this
manual won't make much sense to you.  Reading this Special Topics volume
is optional.


@EndNode

